<HEADLINE> French Open Champ Kuerten out of Contention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- French Open champion Gustavo
Kuerten became the third seeded casualty as he lost 6-4, 6-4 to
Czech Bohdan Ulihrach at the second round of the CA-Trophy tennis
tournament here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The tournament already lost its two top seeds, Yevgeny
Kafelnikov of Russia and Sergi Bruguera of Spain in the first
round.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Kuerten, 21, fifth seed and world No. 11, looked
jaded after his three-set battle against Spain's Albert Costa on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Britons Tim Henman and Greg Rusedski were scheduled to meet
Spain's seventh seed Felix Mantilla and Andrei Medvedev
respectively late Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
