<HEADLINE> Belarus to Develop Friendship With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MINSK, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Belarussian President Alexander
Lukashenko said here today that Belarus will always observe the
principle of developing friendship with China, no matter what the
international situation will be in the future.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko made the remarks when he met a delegation of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) headed by Tomur Dawamat,
vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Speaking highly of the relations between Belarus and China,
Lukashenko said the two countries share a mutual stand on many key
international issues including the issue of human rights.
</P>
<P>
The president said Belarus supports China's position on the
human rights and believed China had scored great achievement in
this field.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope for further boosting economic and trade
relations between Belarus and China.
</P>
<P>
Tomur Dawamat thanked Belarus for its support for China on many
international issues and hoped the two countries will promote
contacts and cooperation in various fields including politics,
economy, and science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The NPC delegation's Belarus tour follows a good-will visit to
Estonia. It will leave for Finland, the last stop of the
three-country visit, this afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
