<HEADLINE> 4 Israeli Soldiers Killed, 7 Wounded in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Four Israeli soldiers were
killed and seven others wounded this afternoon when bombs were
detonated by guerrillas in southern Lebanon, Lebanese radio Voice
of People reported.
</P>
<P>
The radio quoted sources of the South Lebanon Army (SLA),
Israeli militia ally, as saying that the bombs targeted an
Israeli convoy near the village of Markaba, about 500 meters from
the Israeli border in the Israeli-occupied enclave in south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
It said two Israeli soldiers were wounded in the same place by
bombs this morning.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate comment from Israel about the latest
incident in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, guerrillas today fired 25 rocket shells on
the Israeli and SLA's positions in the village, one of which hit
an Israeli target, causing a fuel tank on fire.
</P>
<P>
Security sources said that Israeli troops and SLA militiamen
retaliated with artillery fire on several villages in the
central sector of the occupied zone.
</P>
<P>
The radio said Israeli warplanes were hovering at low
altitude in Saida, 40 kilometers from Beirut.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese guerrillas, including Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or
Party of God, and pro-Syrian Shiite Muslim Movement Amal, are
fighting to oust Israel's 1,200 soldiers and the 2,500 SLA
militiamen from the region of 1,100 square meters in south
Lebanon occupied by Israel in 1985. 
</P>
</TEXT>
