<HEADLINE> Kim Jong Il Becomes Chief of Workers' Party of Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Kim Jong Il, leader of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), today was formally
named general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK).
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by the WPK Central Committee and the
Military Commission of the WPK Central Committee in a "special
report."
</P>
<P>
The report said that WPK members unanimously consider Kim Jong
Il as the great leader who has made the WPK strengthened and
become an all-conquering, experienced and long-tested
revolutionary party, which has won the absolute support and trust
from all people of the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
Kim Jong Il's assumption of the post as general secretary of
the WPK is supported and recognized by all WPK members, it added.
</P>
<P>
In the last 10 days of September and early October, WPK
grass-root organizations at all levels held meetings and adopted
resolutions unanimously naming Kim Jong Il as the party's general
secretary.
</P>
<P>
Since Kim Il Song, former WPK general secretary, passed away on
July 8, 1994, the top post of the WPK has been left vacant for
three years.
</P>
<P>
Kim Jong Il, 55, is a member of the Presidium of the Political
Bureau of the WPK Central Committee, chairman of the Military
Commission of the WPK Central Committee, chairman of the DPRK
National Defense Commission and the supreme commander of the
Korean People's Army.
</P>
<P>
The report highlighted Kim Jong Il's contributions to national
construction of the DPRK and the development of the WPK and the
army, especially the contributions made over last three years
after the death of Kim Il Song.
</P>
<P>
The report said that under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, the
DPRK people will surely overcome all difficulties and hardships
and win the final victory in building the motherland.
</P>
<P>
In the evening, a grand party was held on the Kim Il Song
Square in Pyongyang to celebrate Kim Jong Il's assumption of the
post as WPK general secretary.
</P>
<P>
The party was attended by Ri Jong Ok and Pak Song Chol, DPRK
vice presidents, Kim Yong Nam, vice premier and foreign minister,
Kye Ung Tae, secretary of the secretariat of the WPK central
committee, Cho Myong Rok, director of the general political bureau
of the DPRK armed forces and other DPRK officials, students and
foreign diplomats in Pyongyang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
