<HEADLINE> German Foreign Minister to Visit Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- German Vice Chancellor and Foreign
Minister Klaus Kinkel will pay an official visit to Bulgaria on
October 15 and 16, Bulgarian Foreign Ministry spokesman Radko
Vlaikov announced today.
</P>
<P>
The visit will focus on the policy Bulgaria now pursues and
this country's desire to join the European Union and NATO, Vlaikov
said.
</P>
<P>
These issues as well as bilateral relations will highlight Mr
Kinkel's talks with President Peter Stoyanov, Prime Minister Ivan
Kostov and Foreign Minister Nadezhda Mihailova.
</P>
