<HEADLINE> Angola Urged to Smash Foreign Monopoly of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Angolan Minister of Post and
Telecommunications Licinio Tavares today urged the country's
entrepreneurs to be actively involved into the development of
Angola's post and telecommunications sector.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at the opening ceremony of the first
seminar on policy making of telecommunications sector.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that Angola must set up its own stable and
efficient enterprises to break up the foreign monopoly of
Angola's post and telecommunications sector.
</P>
<P>
New policy for Angola's post and telecommunications sector
should be aimed at establishing high-quality and price-reasonable
networks of post and telecommunications all over the country to
meet the demands of social and economic development, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Tavares added that to realize this goal, the participation of
domestic enterprises in the process must be beefed up while the
role of foreign investment should not be ignored.
</P>
<P>
The seminar will focus its discussions on the state of
Angola's post and telecommunications sector and revise its
development policy to serve the public better, said the minister.
