<HEADLINE> Improvement of Postal Service Urged in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Postal
Organization today called for the improvement of the quality of
postal service in the country in the face of the rapidly changing
global environment.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to mark World Post Day which falls on October
9, the organizaiton said postal services must change with the
global communications market place that is growing more
competitive and diverse every day.
</P>
<P>
According to the organization, an annual total of 430 billion
letters circulate across the world with more than 6.2 million
dedicated postal employees and a network of 700,000 post offices
serving customers around the globe.
</P>
<P>
This year's World Post Day will be celebrated under the theme
''One World, One Postal Network''.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a message issued by Thomas E. Leavey, Director-
General of the International Bureau of the Universal Postal
Union, in connection with the World Post Day pointed out that if
postal administrations do not improve quality of service to meet
customers needs, accept the present communications revolution as
a challenge rather than a threat, start exploring the advantages
of globalization and integrate new technologies, " competing
international postal services will take larger parts of their
core business-physical mail". 
</P>
</TEXT>
