<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A sudden power cut worsened
traffic jam in the Greek capital early this morning following a
failure of the Public Power Corporation's high voltage
distribution centre at Menidi, Attica which knocked out traffic
lights around the capital.
</P>
<P>
The areas worse hit by the power cut which lasted from 6 to 8
a.m. local time were the city center and the northern suburbs.
</P>
<P>
The power cut also caused delays in the operation of dozens of
bakeries in Attica and resulted in a number of people being
trapped in apartment block elevators. 
