<HEADLINE> Nepali Prime Minister Outlines Priorities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Prime Minister Surya
Bahadur Thapa said here today that priorities of his government
include restoring law and order in the country and consolidating
the liberal economy.
</P>
<P>
In a speech in the Lower House, the new prime minister said
his first priority is to protect the life and property of the
people and free the country and the people from the dark shadow of
violence and terror.
</P>
<P>
A campaign to this end will soon be launched effectively, Thapa
said.
</P>
<P>
Over 90 Nepalese have died in the movement launched since
February 1996 by the ultra-leftist guerrillas under the name of
"People's War".
</P>
<P>
Another important responsibility of the government is to
consolidate the liberal, competition-oriented economy, Prime
Minister Thapa said.
</P>
<P>
The government is committed to utilize the skill,
entrepreneurship, capital and managerial expertise of the private
sector to the maximum possible extent in the country within the
liberal economic structure, he said.
</P>
<P>
The government will continue the process of strengthening
industry, commerce, tourism and banking facilities and encourage
private and foreign investment, he added.
</P>
<P>
The government will also consolidate the self governance
through decentralization of powers, means and resources, the new
prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
Thapa won a vote of confidence in the Lower House today. It is
just three days after he took over as head of a new coalition
government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
