<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT October 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM -- Italian playwright Dario Fo won the 1997 Nobel
Literature Prize, the Swedish Academy announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Fo, who wrote "Accidental Death of an Anarchist", won the prize
for this works which "emulates the jesters of the Middle Ages in
scourging authority and upholding the dignity of the
downtrodden," the jury said.
</P>
<P>
Fo, 71, is the 94th Nobel literature laureate. (Nobel-Literature)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi said Thursday that he
was going to submit his resignation to President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro.
</P>
<P>
He made the announcement after the end of a debate in the
Chamber of Deputies over the 17-month-old coalition's economic
policy.
</P>
<P>
Prodi's decision followed his failure to persuade the far-left
Refounded Communists to back the government's budget cuts.
(Italy-Prodi-Resign)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- The World Trade Organization (WTO) Thursday officially
unveiled its logo, which has been absent since the organization
came into being in January 1, 1995.
</P>
<P>
The logo, with six arcs in red, blue and green, is adapted from
the logo initially commissioned for the WTO's first Ministerial
Conference hosted by Singapore last December. (WTO-Logo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- The military junta in Sierra Leone has said the United
Nations Security Council's decision on sanctions against the
country is unfortunate and biased.
</P>
<P>
