<HEADLINE> Russian PM Calls for Economic Cooperation Among CIS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin today called for closer cooperation toward economic
integration within the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS).
</P>
<P>
"A speedy formation of a corresponding transitional
financial-industrial group is essential," Chernomyrdin told a
meeting of the Council of CIS heads of government in Bishkek,
capital of Kirghizstan.
</P>
<P>
He also emphasized the importance of unified policies on
monetary system, transportation and environmental protection
within the 12-member CIS.
</P>
<P>
The CIS, which includes 12 of the 15 former Soviet republics,
was established as the Soviet Union dissolved at the end of
1991. It is intended to preserve and develop ties between the
republics. 
