<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Surging Trade Across the Taiwan Straits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Recent statistics released by
the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation show the
total trade volume between Taiwan region and China's inland areas
hit 12.08 billion US dollars during January-August period, up 7.1
percent on the 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
The inland areas approved a total of 1,381 Taiwan-funded
projects in the first half of this year, with actual allocations
of Taiwan region's investment standing at 1.6 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Statistics through the end of June show that the inland areas
had approved 36,865 Taiwan-funded projects involving total
contracted investments of 35.9 billion US dollars. Taiwan region
ranks the second among overseas investors in China with actual
allocated investments of 16.67 billion US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
