<HEADLINE> Algerian President Ends Visit to Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Algerian President Liamine
Zeroual today ended his visit to Saudi Arabia during which he
gained a pledge from Saudi King Fahd to give a helping hand
in stopping the continued violence in the African country.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day official visit, Zeroual held talks with
Fahd and Saudi Crown Prince and Deputy Prime Minister Abdullah Ibn
Abdul-Aziz, according to Kuwait News Agency.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Fahd expressed readiness to exert efforts in
order to contain the situation in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
More than 60,000 people have been reportedly killed in Algeria
since 1992 when the authorities canceled a general election in
which the radical Islamic Salvation Front took a commanding
lead.
</P>
<P>
The talks, which were held behind closed doors, also
covered ways to promote bilateral relations in the political
and economic fields and the situation on the Arab, Islamic
and international arenas.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also discussed the Middle East peace
process, agreeing on the necessity to resume negotiations on
all tracks in accordance with international resolutions and the
land-for-peace principle.
</P>
<P>
Zeroual arrived in the Saudi Red Sea port city of Jeddah
Tuesday for his first visit to the kingdoms since he assumed power in
1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
