<HEADLINE> Li Peng Pledges Continued Efforts for Sino-US Economic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng pledged that
China will continue efforts to develop Sino-US economic and trade
relations, and noted that the Chinese government has always
assumed a "positive attitude" in this regard.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with US Commerce Secretary William Daley. Li
said that the United States is China's key trade partner, and
noted the vast potential for further cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The premier expressed the hope that both sides will study and
supply each other's needs in order to expand trade relations.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China and the US are countries which have
important influence on the world, and the long-term, healthy and
stable development of their relationship is not only in the
fundamental interests of the two peoples, but also vital to world
peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Li extended a warm welcome to Daley, who is visiting China in
advance of President Jiang Zemin's forthcoming state visit to the
US, He noted that the Chinese government attaches great importance
to Daley's visit.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Premier noted the success of the 11th Session of
the Sino-US Joint Committee on Commerce and Trade (JCCT) which was
co-chaired by Daley and Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and
Economic Co-operation Wu Yi.
</P>
<P>
He said the fact the development momentum of the Chinese
economy is increasing and the investment environment is improving
rapidly will provide countries worldwide, including the US, with
more opportunities for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Daley said President Clinton, the US political community and
the general public are looking forward to President Jiang's state
visit to the US. He said the summit between the heads of state
will bring benefits to both countries.
</P>
<P>
Daley described the 11th Session of the JCCT as a great
success, saying that the two sides will continue consultations on
specific issues related to bilateral economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the US government and industrial and commercial
circles have a positive attitude towards the development of
US-China relations.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that President Jiang's visit will provide
both sides with an opportunity to further expand economic and
trade ties. 
</P>
