<HEADLINE> CIS Leaders Gather for Economic Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Commonwealth of Independent
States (CIS) opened its regular summit meeting today to discuss
economic integration, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Prime ministers of the 12-member CIS reviewed a report
analyzing the economic situation and trend of the bloc at the
meeting held in Bishkek, capital of Kyrghyzstan.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the economic integration within the CIS is to
introduce an economic union between states, including the
setting-up of a tariff union and a payment union.
</P>
<P>
The leaders also discussed plans for coordinating the CIS'
communications policies, setting up a unified agricultural market
and cooperating among border forces of the 12 republics.
</P>
<P>
Military and defense cooperation within the 12 former Soviet
republics was also discussed at the meeting of the CIS Council of
the heads of government, which also opened today. 
</P>
