The President also apprised the delegation of the regional
situation as well as the recent initiatives taken by Pakistani
Prime Minster Nawaz Sharif for "a meaningful dialogue" with India.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the situation in Afghanistan, Leghari said
Pakistan wants peace and stability in Afghanistan. He spoke about
Pakistan's efforts for a durable resolution of the long-running
problem based on the participation of all parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
The President also said Pakistan fully supports UN efforts to
bring about durable peace in the country.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the members of the delegation, Leghari said that
their visit to Pakistan would strengthen the existing friendly
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Describing the relations between the two countries as
excellent, the President stressed the need for enhancing the level
of trade and economic co-operation between Pakistan and South
Africa.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
