<DOCNO> XIE19971009.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Regulates Insurance Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- China's People's Liberation Army
(PLA) recently issued a circular governing army units engaged in
insurance businesses.
</P>
<P>
The circular, jointly issued by the PLA Headquarters of the
General Staff, General Political Department and General Logistics
Department, prohibits PLA units and soliders from conducting
business for local insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
Units which have signed contracts with insurance companies but
are not as yet in business must refrain from related activities
and units already in business should maintain their current scale
and strictly abide by army discipline.
</P>
<P>
Units conducting business with overseas-funded insurance
companies must cease all related activities.
</P>
<P>
The circular prohibits insurance company representatives from
entering off-limits areas and bans the use of all cameras,
video tape-recorders and mapping.  
</P>
</TEXT>
