<HEADLINE> Postcards Mark Universal Postal Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications today issued a set of four commemorative
postcards to mark the 22nd Universal Postal Congress which will be
held in China in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The issuing ceremony was held in the city of Gaoyou in east
China's Jiangsu Province. The city is currently hosting the '97
China Postal Cultural Festival scheduled to end on October 10.
</P>
<P>
The postcards feature the emblem of the 22nd Universal Postal
Congress (4-1), the Great Wall (4-2), beacon fires (4-3) and the
postal service (4-4).  
