<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Bundesbank Raises Repo Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Germany's central bank, the
Bundesbank, announced today a rise in its short-term securities
repurchase interest rate from 3.0 percent to 3.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Being the first increase in the Bundesbank's so-called third
key interest rate since August 1996, the move came as a result of
recent price hikes, indicating that Germany's economy is
recovering from a prolonged slump.
</P>
<P>
But the Bundesbank today still left its two other key interest
rates, the discount rate and the Lombard rate, unchanged at 2.5
percent and 4.5 percent, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
