<HEADLINE> Joint Internet Bookstore Launched in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 9 (Xinhua) -- An Internet bookstore targeting
overseas Chinese has been jointly launched by a Macao company and
a mainland book export company.
</P>
<P>
Internet surfers can reach the "China Modern Bookshop" at the
electronic address of "http://www.modernbooks.com" to get a
glimpse of books and magazines published in China's mainland. They
can also order books through the e-mail service.
</P>
<P>
Johnny Sitou, managing director of the Sunnyland Holding Co.
Ltd., which co-runs the bookstore, said in a press conference
today that the Internet bookshop service has been warmly accepted
by overseas Chinese and those living in Taiwan, Hong Kong and
Macao after it was launched in late August.
</P>
<P>
Currently, his company has got hundreds of orders from Taiwan
and the United States.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 publishing houses in China's mainland have
joined in, he said. It now provides over 15,000 kinds of books and
6,000 kinds of magazines ranging from science, military,
aerospace, medicine, and Qigong and Wushu (martial arts).
</P>
<P>
Sitou said that he plans to expand the service further to
become a global Internet Chinese bookshop where readers can also
find Chinese-language books, magazines and newspapers published in
Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macao and other parts of the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
