<HEADLINE> Germany Allocates $32 Million for Ethiopia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The government of Germany
pledged to commit a total of 32 million US Dollars for funding
Ethiopia's 1997 development cooperation program.
</P>
<P>
This pledge was made today by Rainer Barthelt, Director for
the sub-Saharan Africa with the German Ministry for Economic
Cooperation and Development, at the Ethio-German bilateral
cooperation negotiation meeting here.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, out of
the 32 million US Dollars allocated for development cooperation
program in 1997, 18 million US Dollars could be spent on
technical cooperation and 14 million US Dollars on financial
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, Ethiopian Vice-Minister
of Economic Development and Cooperation Mulatu Teshome said
Ethiopia attaches great importance to Germany's high degree of
involvement in technical and vocational education and training
system through technical and financial cooperation projects.
</P>
</TEXT>
