<HEADLINE> Senior Legislator Promotes Agriculture Law in Ningxia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Senior legislator Buhe today
urged local officials in northwest China to better publicize and
carry out the Agriculture Law.
</P>
<P>
Buhe, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee, also noted in his inspection of the Ningxia
Hui Autonomous Region, northwest China, that farmers should be
more aware of the law so as to safeguard their legal rights.
</P>
<P>
He said that local law enforcement departments should improve
their work, and that local people's congresses should formulate
supportive regulations and intensify their supervision over the
implementation of the law.
</P>
<P>
More efforts should be made to reduce the burden of farmers,
more money should be invested in agriculture, and a farm produce
circulation system in line with the market economy should be
established, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the legislator placed an emphasis on an equal
and united relations between different ethnic groups and mutual
assistance among them, so as to promote their common prosperity.
</P>
</TEXT>
