<HEADLINE> Germany Sees Mexico As "Ideal Partner", Kinkel Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 9 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel said here today that Mexico is a "ideal partner" for
Germany to seek closer cooperation with the Latin American region.
</P>
<P>
"Mexico is a door for the German industry to Latin America, as
well as the United States and Canada. Meanwhile, Germany is Latin
America's door in the European Union and the bridge to Central and
Eastern Europe," said Kinkel during a meeting here today with
visiting Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo.
</P>
<P>
