<HEADLINE> Chinese Mayor Gets UN Human Settlement Prize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHONGSHAN, GUANGDONG, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Huang Ziqiang,
mayor of Zhongshan city was given a special award for his
contribution to human settlement work by the United Nation here
today.
</P>
<P>
Since 1986, the local government has input some 900 million
yuan (about 110 million US dollars) to build 7,831 affordable
apartments totaling 1.07 million square meters, which helped the
low-income families get their own houses.
</P>
<P>
They also took advantage of the investment from different
sources to build another 51,300 affordable apartments of 6.86
million sq.m..
</P>
<P>
Now the average per capita urban living space has hit 20.2
sq.m. in Zhongshan, whose average per capita rural living space
has reached 32.3 sq.m..
</P>
<P>
The city government was also praised for its effort to make
the local environment better.
</P>
<P>
Huang Ziqiang said that Zhongshan not only will continue to
develop its economy, but also protect its natural resources and
environment. 
</P>
