<HEADLINE> Ramos Approves Implementation of Industrial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
has approved the implementation of an industrial development plan
to boost the country's bid to achieve Newly-Industrializing
Country status by the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
The Industrial Development Plan of the Philippines aims to
further enhance the global competitiveness of the local
industries, the Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
It has identified 17 "must have" industry sectors where the
country has competitive advantage, the report said.
</P>
<P>
These sectors include copper, decorative craft, electronics,
fertilizer, footwear and leather goods, fresh fruits, furniture,
garments and textiles.
</P>
<P>
Industrial tree plantation, iron and steel industry, marine
products, motor vehicle and components, natural rubber,
oleochemicals, petrochemicals, processed food are also included.
</P>
<P>
Ramos directed concerned agencies to submit to the Industry
Development Council the appropriate action plan on the effective
and efficient implementation of their respective components of the
Industrial Development Plan.
</P>
<P>
He also tasked the council to conduct an annual review of the
plan, in coordination with concerned government agencies and the
private sector, to ensure the plan's responsiveness to the
national thrusts and world developments.  
</P>
