<HEADLINE> Uganda's 35th Independence Anniversary Marked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Celebrations were held held in
the Ugandan capital of Kampala today to mark the country's 35th
anniversary of independence.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of Ugandans from all walks of life and
diplomatic envoys here attended the celebration activities which
were presided over by Ugandan president yoweri museveni. The
visiting Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa were also on the
occassion.
</P>
<P>
In a nationwide speech to mark the Independence Day, Ugandan
President Yoweri Museveni called on the countrymen to work hard
to eradicate poverty prevailing in the country.
</P>
<P>
The president said that in order to fight poverty, the Ugandan
government will soon launch a poverty eradication action plan.
</P>
<P>
the plan focuses on key sectors involving in road maintenance,
agricultural modernization, primary education, health care and
promotion of the private sector.
</P>
<P>
A major component of the plan is to open up roads in the rural
areas by upgrading the existing trunk and construction of feed
roads in accordance with a 10-year road development program, the
president said.
</P>
<P>
Museveni said that the government has finalized a plan for
agricultural modernization.
</P>
<P>
On economic situation in the country, the Ugandan president
said that during the fiscal year 1996/97, Uganda's economy grew
only by 5 percent,which was lower than the previous four years
due to mainly the prolonged dry weather condition.
</P>
<P>
During 1996/97, he said, total agriculture output accounted
for 44.1 percent of the Gross Domestic Product as compared to 57
percent in 1987/88, while the manufactural sector, now accounts
for about 8.4 percent of the total economic output as compared to
5.8 percent in 1987/88.
</P>
<P>
The manufactural sector grew by 14.2 percent during 1996/97.
</P>
<P>
Non-coffee exports earned the country 272 U.S. Dollars during
1996/97, an increase of 45 percent in comparision with that in
1995/96.
</P>
<P>
On the international issues, Museveni called on sudan to stop
supporting Uganda's rebels in distabilizing the country.
</P>
<P>
He siad that Uganda supports the sanctions imposed on Burundi
for recovering constitutional order in that country but not for
sanction against the Burundi people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
