<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank Receives Overseas Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC), the nation's biggest commercial bank, has
obtained an overseas syndicated loan of 37.69 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Carrying a preferential interest rate, the six-year loan will
be directed into eight technical renovation projects in the
automobile, chemical, iron and steel and electronics industries in
China, according to the bank officials.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-President of the ICBC Li Lihui said at the loan
agreement signing ceremony that his bank is bound to increase its
effort to raise capital overseas, and step up cooperation with
overseas banks to support the technical renovation of the domestic
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC had its foreign exchange assets worth 27.7 billion US
dollars at the end of June, including 10.4 billion US dollars in
foreign exchange deposits.
</P>
<P>
The bank made 540 million US dollars in profits last year, with
international settlement business valued at 56 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Since 1988, the ICBC has clinched more than 150 loan agreements
with banks in Japan, Singapore, Britain, Italy, Austria,
Switzerland, Germany and the United States, channeling nearly 800
million US dollars into more than 200 projects in China. 
</P>
