<HEADLINE> Four Sets of Army Regulations Revised </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, chairman of the
Central Military Commission, has issued an order to put into
effect four sets of revised regulations on interior service,
discipline, formation drilling and garrison concerning the
People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
Original regulations were issued in the early 1990s, while the
new ones better carry out China's military strategy in the new
period and draw in the successful experience in the course of the
army building and reform over the past years, military sources
said.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the new regulations will ensure the absolute
leadership of the Communist Party of China over the army, fully
implement the policies worked out at the just-ended 15th National
Party Congress, and raise the army's combat effectiveness.
</P>
<P>
The new Regulation on Internal Service is to strengthen the
army's interior management, including new chapters on exchanges
with the outside, the usage of the national flag and playing and
singing of the national anthem.
</P>
<P>
The Regulation on Discipline places greater stress on reward
and punishment. The Regulation on Formation standardizes and
stipulates some basic formation actions.
</P>
<P>
The regulation on garrison makes it more explicit the task,
responsibility and system in terms of guard and garrison, together
with more articles on safeguarding the army's fame and the legal
rights of armymen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
