<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Triple Olympian Xiong Xi won
the gold medal in the men's three-meter springboard finals at the
Eighth National Games here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Ni, now reprenting Hunan province, won the title with a
total of 735.30 points, followed by local diver Wang Tianling with
696.24 and Zhou Yilin of Shanxi province with 691.47.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old made his debut nine years ago by winning a
silver in the 10-meter platform in the Seoul Olympic Games,
narrowly losing to legend diver Greg Louganis of the United
States.
</P>
<P>
He took a bronze in the same event four years later in
Barcelona and ultimately realized his golden dream in Atlanta,
where he captured the gold from the three-meter springboard.
