<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined on the
Singapore market today as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index lost 20.57 points to close at 1861.46 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 174.53 million units, valued
at 347.53 million Singapore dollars (about 224.21 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 244 to 86, while 288
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MBf Capital was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 11.71 million units. It was followed by
Rekapac which had 8.81 million shares traded. RHB Capital
Warrant99 was next with 8.49 million units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 50 cents to finish at 21.7 Singapore
dollars. Datacraft gained 38 cents to end at 2.74 U.S. dollars,
while the Malaya Banking 200 increased by 30 cents to close at 8.6
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Thai Prime Fund was the biggest loser as
it declined by 25 cents to end at 6.55 U.S. dollars. Cerebos fell
by 22 cents to close at 4.88 Singapore dollars. The Sembawang
Corporation, the Singapore Land, and the United Overseas Bank
(UOB) lost 20 cents each to finish at 5.7, 6.35, and 8.7 Singapore
dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
