<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Dario Fo Wins Nobel Literature Prize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Italian playwright Dario Fo
won the 1997 Nobel Literature Prize, the Swedish Academy
announced today.
</P>
<P>
Fo, who wrote "Accidental Death of an Anarchist",won the prize
for this works which "emulates the jesters of the Middle Ages in
scourging authority and upholding the dignity of the
downtrodden," the jury said.
</P>
<P>
"For many years Fo has performed all over the world, perhaps
more than any other contemporary dramatist, and his influence has
been considerable. He if anyone merits the epithet of jester in
the true meaning of that word," it said.
</P>
<P>
Fo, 71, is the 94th Nobel literature laureate.
</P>
<P>
The jury described Fo as an "extremely serious satirist with a
multifaceted oeuvre."
</P>
<P>
Fo will receive the record prize sum of 7.5 million kronor (one
million dollars) at the official prize ceremony in Stockholm on
December 10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
