<HEADLINE> Fujian to Boost Electronics Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
plans to achieve an annual increase of nearly 29 percent in its
electronics industrial output value before year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The production value of the electronics industry is projected
to reach 50 billion yuan annually by 2010, eight to ten percent of
the total of the country's electronics industry, according to
China Electronics News.
</P>
<P>
Fujian's electronic industry is expected to export 1.6 billion
US dollars worth-of goods a year then.
</P>
<P>
By 2010, the provincial government plans to expand the domestic
and international market share of its electronics industry and
will focus on the introduction of overseas funds, technology and
managerial expertise.
</P>
<P>
Fujian's electronics industry will also concentrate on the
development of information technology, with special attention
being given to consumer goods like audio and visual equipment,
computers, telecommunications equipment, and monitors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
