<HEADLINE> S. Africa Becomes Top Investor in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 9 (Xinhua) -- South African companies
have overtaken the British as the biggest investors in Zambia,
local daily Business Day quoted a statistics made by Zambia
Investment Center as reporting today.
</P>
<P>
The total investment pledged by South Africa has topped 180
million U.S. Dollars against 125 million dollars by Britain, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Jerome Mweetwa, senior project development officer for the
Zambian Investment Center said a survey indicated 60 percent of
investments pledged by South Africa had already been realized.
</P>
<P>
Mweetwa, based in Pretoria to promote business and industrial
cooperation between Zambia and South African enterprises, said a
number of Zambian businesses were seeking partnerships or
alliances with South Africans because they needed capital or
expertise.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that Zambia had freed the repatriation of
profits. 
</P>
