<HEADLINE> Russian Firm Considers Bus Assembly Plant in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Joint Stock Company, a Russian
bus manufacturer, is now considering setting up a bus assembly
plant in Nigeria, the Daily Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
An official of the company was quoted as saying recently at the Lagos
Motorfair that with the increasing acceptability of its PAZ range of
city bus and other products, it is certain that an assembly plant is
feasible.
</P>
<P>
Joint Stock, the official claimed, is one of the largest
medium-sized bus producer in Europe and is capable of providing
14,000 buses a year.
</P>
<P>
The company has introduced three kinds of buses in Lagos, Yola
and Kano cities, but the exact amount of sales are not known.
</P>
<P>
"When our sales reach 1,000 plus mark, we will do something
concrete about the proposed assembly plant," the official said.
</P>
