<HEADLINE> World Trade Centers Association Introduces TradeCard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Trade Centers
Association (WTCA), a non-government organization for the
promotion of global trade, will introduce a new electronic card to
"make trade more efficient", WTCA President Guy Tozzoli said
today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference after the conclusion of the 28th
WTCA General Assembly, Tozzoli said that the TradeCard, "the
world's first credit card for international trade", will be issued
in the next 60 days after being tested for a year.
</P>
<P>
The card is a "revolutionary new trading tool" which operates
on personal computers, he said, noting that it will benefit
importers, exporters, bankers and transporters.
</P>
<P>
The WTCA and the General Electric have signed a strategic
partnership on the TradeCard, he added.
</P>
<P>
He described the four-day general assembly as a great success.
Hong Kong has always been a great place for the members of the
WTCA to trade and will continue to be so in the future, maybe even
better, he said.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Hong Kong for the 55th time, Tozzoli commented that
there is almost no change in the city except for the difference in
the flag flying over.
</P>
<P>
The WTCA was founded in 1960 by Tozzoli to help small and
medium-sized companies engage in international trade. It grouped
only 16 member cities of seven countries at that time.
</P>
<P>
Now it boasts 318 member cities in 97 countries worldwide and
services over 500,000 businesses.
</P>
<P>
The assembly, with the theme "Windows on World Trade", included
training sessions, professional briefings and site visits. Wu Yi,
Chinese minister of foreign trade and economic cooperation, made a
keynote speech at the opening ceremony of the assembly.
</P>
<P>
The 29th WTCA General Assembly will be held in Santiago, Chile,
next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
