<HEADLINE> HK to Open New Bridge Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to open its
1,177-meter-long Ting Kau Bridge in mid-1998 to provide an
alternative access to Lantau Link, which leads to Hong Kong's new
airport at Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the project said today that erection of the
bridge's 170 deck units, each weighing 50 tons, was in good
progress. Construction of the approach viaducts and ramps is
nearing completion.
</P>
<P>
Costing 1,740 million HK dollars (223 million U.S. dollars),
the bridge is a cable-stayed bridge with three bridge towers up to
194 meters high and with a three carriage-way of 18.8 meters in
width in each direction.
</P>
<P>
Spanning over the 900-meter-wide Ramble Channel, the Ting Kau
Bridge will rank among the longest cable-stayed bridges in the
world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
