<HEADLINE> Scientific and Technical Park In East China For Taiwan Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A new scientific and technical
industrial park geared toward Taiwan investors was set up recently
in Nanjing, the capital of China's Jiangsu province, with approval
from the Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council and the State
Science and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
It is situated in the Nanjing Economic Development Zone on 3.5
square kilometers of land, and has been divided into several
sections for finance, warehousing, and research and development.
</P>
<P>
Industries in the prior agenda of the district include
electronics and information, modern telecom, bio-engineering, new
materials and fine chemicals.
</P>
<P>
The park expects to have 25 billion yuan in turnover by the end
of the century, 60 percent of that from high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
By the end of August, there were 405 enterprises already in the
park, including 28 wholly funded by Taiwan investors and 109 with
other overseas investment. Combined overseas investment in the
region is 800 million US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
