<HEADLINE> Tung's Policy Address Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Policy Address delivered
by Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) Tung Chee Hwa was hailed by local newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Most newspapers printed the full text of the Address, and
devoted pages to discussing and commenting on the first Policy
Address of the SAR.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Commercial Daily said in its editorial that the
Address outlined the prospects of Hong Kong in the 21st century,
and designed programs for industrial development, information
technology, housing, education, social welfare and some other
issues.
</P>
<P>
An editorial in Wen Wei Po said that a major difference between
Tung's Address and those made by the former British Hong Kong
governors is that Tung's looks at things from a long-term point of
view with overall considerations, while the latter ones were often
short-sighted and favored instant benefits.
</P>
<P>
Ta Kung Pao commented that the Address represents the spirit of
"one country, two systems", and is full of the feeling of "loving
the motherland, loving Hong Kong". It is progressive and full of
confidence, bringing people a message that Hong Kong is welcoming
its new era.
</P>
<P>
Commentaries in many newspapers also pointed out that the
British colonial rule has left the SAR government with many
difficult problems, such as housing, quality of education, boat
people and social welfare. Tung's Address designed programs and
set target for resolving these problems, which are both practical
and feasible.
</P>
<P>
Newspapers also published reaction from local organizations,
social communities and individuals, many of them expressed
welcome to Tung's Address and some of them also gave their
suggestions regarding the working programs outlined in the
Address.  
</P>
</TEXT>
