<HEADLINE> Taiwan Authorities Urged to Make "Correct Choice" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A well-known businessman in Macao
today urged the Taiwan authorities to make a correct historical
choice in the interests of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Ma Man Kei, president of the Macao Chamber of Commerce, said at
a gathering marking the 86th anniversary of the "Revolution of
1911," which overthrew the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911), that the
Taiwan authorities should abandon its splitting activities, and
achieve reunification with the mainland on the basis of the "one
country, two systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the Taiwan authorities would make a correct
historical choice, joining hands (with the Communist Party of
China) in achieving reunification and prosperity of the Chinese
nation by seeking common grounds under the principle of 'one
China' and the policy of 'one country, two systems,'" he said at
the ceremony attended by more than 100 celebrities and
representatives in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Also executive chairman of the presidium of the Committee for
the Celebration of the 48th Anniversary of the Founding of the
People's Republic of China, Ma blasted the Taiwan authorities for
"trumpeting 'Taiwan independence,'" which he said has blocked the
process of peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
"The splitting cliques in the Taiwan island and the
interference by some anti-China foreign powers have severely
hindered the process of peaceful reunification," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Taiwan authorities have been wantonly trumpeting 'Taiwan
independence', creating 'two Chinas' or 'one China, one Taiwan.'
They have betrayed the interests of the Chinese nation, and are
naturally met with resolute opposition from the Chinese people as
a whole, including the Taiwan compatriots," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
