<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Prudence in Japan-US Security Cooperation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- China today urged Japan and the
United States to "act with prudence" in their cooperation under
the new Japan-US defense cooperation guidelines.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang made the call at a
weekly news conference when he was asked by Xinhua to respond to
the recent China visit by Japan's Deputy Vice-Foreign Minister
Minolu Tanbu.
</P>
<P>
Shen said Tanbu visited China October 8 for the purpose of
briefing and explaining to the Chinese side the new Japan-US
defense cooperation guidelines on behalf of the Japanese
government.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan listened to his
briefing, Shen said.
</P>
<P>
According to Shen, the Japanese side made it clear during the
briefing that Japan would, in its defense cooperation with the US
under the new guidelines, adhere to the policy of defense limited
to its own territory and coastal waters and three non-nuclear
principles in conformity with its peace constitution, and act in
strict observance of the UN charter and norms of international
laws.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese side made an explanation on the concept of
"surrounding situation" in the new guidelines, saying that it is
not a geographical concept but rather a concept pertaining to the
nature of the events that would have major impact on Japan's peace
and security. Japan will never use force outside its own
territory, unless it it is attacked by military forces. Shen said.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese side went on to assure the Chinese side that it
would not support "two Chinas" or Taiwan independence and that it
would continue to observe all the principles set forth in the
Japan-China Joint Statement and Japan-China Treaty of Peace and
Friendship, Shen said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side made a comprehensive elaboration of its views
and position on the new guidelines. It pointed out that the
Japan-US security cooperation mechanism was a bilateral
arrangement that was evolved under the specific historical
conditions of the Cold War era, Shen said.
</P>
<P>
Today, Shen went on, as the international situation is in
general moving towards relaxation, this arrangement should all the
more be kept within the bilateral framework.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971009.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Prudence in Japan-US Security Cooperation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese side considers the elaboration and explanation made
by the Japanese side on the term surrounding situation as "obscure
and unconvincing," the spokesman noted.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese side has repeatedly stated that the Japan-US
security cooperation has not been expanded in scope and neither is
it directed against any third country. However, it has also said
that it is unable to geographically define the surrounding
situation, Shen said.
</P>
<P>
In other words, Shen added, the geographical sphere of the
surrounding situation can in reality be determined and expanded at
will. The Chinese side expressed its concern over the provision in
the new guidelines for Japan's military role outside its
territory, and hoped that Japan would draw lessons from history,
honor its commitment to development through peace instead of
striving to become a military power.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side stressed that a major reason for China's
concern with the guidelines was that it involved Taiwan issue,
Shen said.
</P>
<P>
China's position on the question of Taiwan is firm and
consistent, he noted. The Chinese government and people find it
absolutely unacceptable for the Japan-US defense cooperation to
cover the Taiwan region directly or indirectly.
</P>
<P>
Since the Japanese government has made commitment on the
question of Taiwan in the Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and
Sino-Japanese Treaty of Peace and Friendship, we hope that the
Japanese side will honor its words, highly respect the Chinese
position on the question of Taiwan, and strictly abide by the
relevant principles and spirit enshrined in the above-mentioned
two documents, Shen said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side hopes that both Japan and the US, when
conducting cooperation under the new guidelines, will "take care
of the concerns and worries of the neighboring countries in Asia,
including China, take into serious consideration the general trend
of peace and development in the Asia-Pacific region, and act with
prudence, so as not to cause concern and uneasiness to the
surrounding countries or further complicate the security situation
of this region," the spokesman noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
