<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0630 GMT October 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST -- The North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)
Thursday started a war game at a Romanian military base in
Constanta, on the coast of the Black Sea.
</P>
<P>
The entire game on marine logistic support for peacekeeping
operations was to be carried out on paper, and was the first of
such kind of simulation held outside the NATO 16 member nations.
</P>
<P>
Joining the game, code-named Cooperative Support '97, were nine
countries from the Western military bloc and an equal number of
members of NATO's Partnership for Peace program from East
Europe. (Romania-NATO-War Game)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HAVANA -- Cuban President Fidel Castro insisted Thursday that a
Miami-based Cuban exile group, the Cuban American National
Foundation (CANF), organized a series of small bomb attacks at
hotels in Havana over the last five months.
</P>
<P>
"All these explosions were organized by the Cuban-American
Foundation and we know enough about this and we are absolutely
sure and we can categorically affirm it, there is no doubt,"
Castro, quoted by the Cuban news agency Prensa Latina, said.
</P>
<P>
Castro was speaking at the opening of the Communist Party's
Fifth Party Congress in Havana. His address was a seven-hour
review of Cuba's economic and political policy in recent
years. (Cuba-Party Congress)
</P>
