<HEADLINE> Camel Disease Spotted Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Camel disease has surfaced
in Shinile area of Somali region of Ethiopia, according to a
report from the Ethiopian News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted doctor Mohammed Said Hassan, an official
from the Somali Regional Agricultural Bureau as saying that a
team of experts deployed at the area has confirmed that the
disease affecting the respiratory organ of the animals has
surfaced near the border with afar region.
</P>
<P>
The doctor said even though the exact figure of affected
camels is so far unknown, a number of them are dying every day.
</P>
<P>
The Somali Regional Agricultural Bureau is preparing to launch
a vaccination campaign in cooperation with the Ministry of Health
to contain the spread of the disease to other areas of the
region, the doctor added.  
</P>
