<HEADLINE> Coach Ma Junren not Included in National Games Roster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Ma Junren, who coached "Ma
Family Army" to sweep nearly all women's middle and long distance
golds in major international meets in 1993, was not included in
the roster of Liaoning delegation for the upcoming Eighth National
Games.
</P>
<P>
Ma was a surpring absentee from the name list of the delegation
which consists all of the athletes, officials and coaches, sources
from the organizing committee revealed on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Yet, the legendary coach's 30 proteges will take part in the
National Games which will raise its curtain here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the "mysterious" coach could make an
unexpected appearance in the Games.
</P>
<P>
Early this year, Ma was also not included in the track team
list in the qualifying round, but he was there eventually.
</P>
<P>
The big names among his disciples are Liu Dong and Qu Yunxia,
both won gold medals in the 1993 World Athletics Championships in
Stuggart.
</P>
<P>
His most glittering star deciple Wang Junxia, who won the
women's 5,000-meter gold in Atlanta and still holds the world
10,000-meter record, will not participate in the National Games
due to an injury.
</P>
<P>
Wang, along with Liu, broke away from coach Ma in 1994 because
Ma reportedly refused to give them the Mercedes Benz cars which
they won as a gift at Stuttgart. The two talented women athletes
are nowsdays coached by Mao Dezhen.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1994 Asian Games, Ma has been coaching a new army
inluding many teenage runners, and over 30 of them qualified for
the National Games.
</P>
<P>
To prepare for the Games, he led the army to the high-altitude
Duoba training center in Qinghai province, the ninth time he had
been there prior to the major competitions.
</P>
<P>
In fact, people all around the country expect him to creat
another miracle after the Chinese athletes failed to win a single
medal in the sixth World Athletics Championships in Athlens in
August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
