<HEADLINE> Tibet Establishes Computer Tax Collection Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A computer tax collection network
has been established in seven prefectures and cities in the Tibet
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
A computer center run by the tax collection department in
Lhasa, the regional capital, is connected to tax offices at the
grass-roots level.
</P>
<P>
Tax revenues have been a problem for the local government,
because of the region's vast territory and the fact that there are
many prefectures on the high plateau.
</P>
<P>
The Tibet tax bureau started the trial use of computers in
three offices last November, and one official says that his bureau
has collected more taxes thanks to the computer system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
