<HEADLINE> Sydney Organisers to Sell 2000 Olympic Coins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Sydney Games organisers
unveiled a collection of gold, silver and bronze Olympic coins on
Thursday, the world's first coins to carry the date 2000.
</P>
<P>
The first of a series of 52 coins will be placed on the
international market next month as the first Sydney Olympic
merchandise to be sold overseas.
</P>
<P>
Nine coins released on Thursday include six aluminium-bronze
coins featuring six of the 28 summer Olympic sports: archery,
hockey, athletics, sailing, weightlifting and gynmnastics. Coins
covering the remaining sports will be released over the next
three years.
</P>
<P>
Also unveiled were two silver coins representing cultural
and environmental themes and the first of an eight-coin gold
series featuring the Olympic flame and Games logo. 
</P>
