<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Recapture Road from Rebel Hands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's government troops
this morning recaptured the Mankaulam-Mullaitivu road in Northern
province after several days of heavy fighting with the Tamil
rebels, a military spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Sarath Munasinghe told a press conference this
morning that casualties in the fighting for recapturing the road
were still not known so far.
</P>
<P>
The road, which had been controlled by the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) since June last year, is of vital importance
for the government to transport goods from the center of Northern
province to the eastern part of the province.
</P>
<P>
The 50-kilometer road lies at the north of Puliyankulam town,
where the government troops have been fighting with the rebels for
nearly two months.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 14-year war for a separate state
in the north and east of the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
