<HEADLINE> Zambia Drug Officials Hold 9 Somalis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Nine Somali nationals have been
arrested in Ndola, 280 kilometers north of the capital, for
trafficking in psychotropic substances, Zambia Daily Mail
reported today.
</P>
<P>
They were arrested by the Drug Enforcement Commission in Ndola
for allegedly trafficking 65 grams of dagga and 1868 grams of
cathine, also known as miraa or khat without authority on
September 29.
</P>
<P>
Cathine is normally chewed to keep awake, particularly by
long-distance truckers.
</P>
<P>
The offenders, including 3 women, will appear in court for plea
today, according to the paper.  
</P>
