<HEADLINE> Uganda's Manufacturing Sector Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The manufacturing sector in
Uganda has grown by 28 percent, with 2,275 investment licenses
issued since July 1991, reported the local press today.
</P>
<P>
It has 619 projects valuing at 991 million U.S. Dollars and
providing 37,330 jobs.
</P>
<P>
The sector contributed 8.3 percent of Gross Domestic Product
(GDP) in 1995/96 up from 4.2 percent in 1986. The overall
production in January this year was 30.7 percent higher than
January 1996 while the growth for the first seven months this
year was 22.9 percent higher than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the growth is the country's policies for
encouraging investors to invest in the sector and the peace and
stability situation prevailing across the country for the last 11
years. 
</P>
