<HEADLINE> Poverty-relief Efforts in South Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou Paper
Manufacturing Group Ltd opened here Wednesday, but there was no
ceremony to mark the occasion - because it donated the money set
aside for that to a poverty-relief program.
</P>
<P>
The group donated 200,000 yuan (about 25,000 US dollars) for
building a primary school in the Baise region in the Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region of southwest China, one of the country's
18 poverty-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Guangzhou was given the task of helping the region
fight poverty, and the city has donated 30 million yuan to help
10,000 villagers. Various means have been employed to help develop
the region. The city's women's federation has collected about
150,000 yuan for Baise's poverty-relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
During the Spring Festival (the lunar new year), city
government leaders went to the region to extend greetings to local
people and to bring 300,000 yuan in relief funds. The city's
Garden Hotel helped two villages in the region solve their water
and electricity supply problems.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the scale has grown. City departments and
enterprises have signed 27 co-operation agreements with the Baise
Region to help it develop breeding, planting, agricultural product
processing, and building materials businesses.  
</P>
