<HEADLINE> Kenya's Trade within Africa in Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's trade with other
African countries has seen a dramatic rise in the last four
years, the Kenya Times newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Forty-seven percent of the country's exports and ten percent
of its imports last year were in Africa, Permanent Secretary in
the Ministry of Planning and National Development Edwin Osundwa
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The figures are in contrast with those in 1993, when only 2.3
percent of Kenya's imports were from Africa and 34 percent of
exports went to the continent, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he called for further cooperation among African
countries, noting regional cooperation results in higher income
for citizens, higher foreign investment and expanded market.
</P>
