<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 07:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Process Tapping Sea-wave Power Invented </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 9 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli company announced
it has invented a new process for environmentally friendly and
inexpensive production of electricity and desalinated water by
using sea wave.
</P>
<P>
According to local report today, the new process, which is
under the United States patent, was developed by the SDF company,
a small, start-up company based in Tel Aviv.
</P>
<P>
Having completed a successful working model for the production
of 1,500 watts, SDE has received financial backing from the Office
of Israel's Chief Scientist under the Ministry of Industry and
Trade.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to build a four megawatt installation on a
tract of coastal land in the Mediterranean coastal city Ashdod,
about 50 kilometers southwest of Tel Aviv, within six to eight
months.
</P>
<P>
Scientists estimated that sea-wave power can potentially supply
up to 15 percent of the world's electrical needs, as well as
desalinated water for countries with sea coasts but facing fresh
water shortages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
