<HEADLINE> Identification of Health Priorities In Africa and </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 9 (Xinhua) -- African and Asian
countries have been urged to identify areas of health priorities
on which local or foreign resources can be spent cost
effectively.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by Tanzanian Minister for Health Aaron
Chiduo when opening the seventh meeting of the International
Health Policy Program for Asian and African countries in Arusha
on Wednesday, according to a news dispatch from the northern
Tanzanian town available here today.
</P>
