<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Export Continues to Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's export in the first
two months of the current fiscal year (July 1, 1997- June 30,
1998) stood at 922 million U.S. dollars against the target of 833
million dollars, according to an official handout here today.
</P>
<P>
This is 20.83 percent increase over the export value of July
and August of 1996 and about 30 percent above that of the
corresponding two months of 1995.
</P>
<P>
Export target of the current fiscal year has been fixed at 5
billion dollars against the total export of 1996-97 at 4.42
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The total export of 1995-96 was 3.86 billion dollars. The last
two months' export value was also 10.62 percent higher than the
target, the handout said.
</P>
<P>
Export of jute has been increased by 41.54 percent in
July-August over the corresponding period of 1996, while
ready-made garment and frozen food exports increased by 33 and
12.52 percent respectively.  
</P>
