<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian to Build New Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 9 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian province has
gotten approval from the State Planning Commission to build a
154-km highway as part of an improved transportation system in
southeastern parts of the province.
</P>
<P>
The highway links the capital, Fuzhou, with the coastal city of
Quanzhou. It is expected to open in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The project, along with another 16-km highway, is estimated to
cost 4.67 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province has built a highway linking Quanzhou with Xiamen,
and construction work on a highway linking Xiamen with Zhangzhou
is expected to be finished within the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
