<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
shrugged off the fall on Wall Street overnight with many leaders
moving higher in afternoon trading today.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 5 points higher at 2597 with a turnover
of 75 million NZ dollars (48 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Energy led the rises, jumping 17 cents to 703 cents
after the company announced it would supply the NZ Electricity
Corporation with gas for 17 years after 2000. Other leaders to
gain included Air New Zealand, edging up 1c to 282c, Carter Holt
Harvey, rising 3c to 355c and Lion Nathan, climbing 9c to 390c.
</P>
<P>
However, market leader Telecom remained unchanged at 816c, so
did Brierley Investment at 137c.
</P>
<P>
Overall, the market tone was weaker with 39 rises against 59
falls.  
</P>
</TEXT>
