<HEADLINE> Bangladesh PM to Attend Commonwealth Summit in UK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina is expected to seize the opportunity to hold bilateral
talks with more than a dozen heads of state and government during
the forthcoming Commonwealth summit, said Foreign Ministry
sources.
</P>
<P>
Hasina will leave Dhaka on October 23 to attend the
Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting, which will begin on
October 24 in Edinburgh, Scotland, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
It is informed that Queen Elizabeth II, head of the
Commonwealth, will inaugurate the four-day conference of the loose
confederation of former British colonies, to be participated by
heads of government of 53 member countries.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the conference, Sheikh Hasina is likely to exchange
views on bilateral matters as well as regional and international
issues of common concern with leaders from south Africa, Sri
Lanka, India, Pakistan and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
She is also likely to have bilateral meetings with British
Prime Minister Tony Blair and the heads of government of Canada,
Australia and New Zealand, the sources added.  
</P>
