<HEADLINE> Epidemics Kill Over One Hundred in Southern Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Over 100 people have died from
dengue fever and typhoid is plaguing the southern part of Vietnam
now, the newspaper Vietnam News said today.
</P>
<P>
The government is making efforts to contain the spread of the
diseases, the English daily said.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics indicate that typhoid and dengue fever have
killed 12 and 125 people respectively in the last nine months.
</P>
<P>
Some 11,225 people have contracted dengue fever and 44,622 have
contracted typhoid.
</P>
<P>
The daily said many localities are encountering difficulties in
preventing the two epidemics.
</P>
<P>
In the hard-hit province of Tra Vinh, 8,363 people have been
affected by the diseases. 62 have died since the beginning of the
year.
</P>
<P>
Unsanitary conditions are blamed for the rapid spread of the
two diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
