<HEADLINE> Four Italian Journalists Detained in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Four Italian journalists were
detained by Turkish authorities today in the Black Sea port of
Fatsa while the four were filming a report for a Swiss television,
the Italian Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign ministry said it has asked Turkey to explain the
reason of the detention.
</P>
<P>
It said the journalists had obtained the necessary
authorization to carry out their work in Fatsa.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministry officials said they have not received any
response from the Turkish government or from the Turkish embassy
in Rome.
</P>
<P>
An Italian embassy official will travel to Fatsa Thursday for
the resolution of the case, according to the foreign ministry.
</P>
