<HEADLINE> More Myanmar Nurses to Be Employed in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Singapore will employ 32 more
Myanmar nurses under a cooperation program jointly initiated by
the health ministries of Myanmar and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar nurses will fully enjoy the benefits prescribed by
the employing country, official paper The New Light of Myanmar
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Singapore recognizes the services of qualified Myanmar nurses,
and all the nurses of the first batch sent to Singapore in 1994
have passed the international examinations and got registered, the
report quoted Myanmar Minister for Health U Saw Tun as saying.
</P>
<P>
The employment of Myanmar nurses in Singapore is another
cooperation program between Myanmar and Singapore in the health
sector in recent years. Singapore has also conducted some training
programs for Myanmar trainees for hotels and tourism, and trade
management.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
