<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Eyes Larger Share in World Shipping Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Ports Authority
(PPA) will implement various programs to enable the country to
grab a larger share in the global shipping industry, the
Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
PPA General Manager Carlos Agustin said that the measures
include building adequate seaport infrastructure, encouraging
international shipbuilding and ship repair companies to locate
their operation and strengthening the training of human resources
in the industry.
</P>
<P>
The PPA will also invite companies to participate in
formulating development goals for the marine sector to satisfy the
prerequisites for becoming a major transshipment center, he said.
</P>
<P>
The efforts are also aimed at preventing the country from
further suffering from any setbacks in light of the recent slide
in world port ranking from the 16th place to the 18th, Agustin
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
