<HEADLINE> Thai Police Link Officials to Drug Deals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Thai police are keeping a close
watch on some senior government officials suspected of having lent
their official cars to drug gangs to help them avoid a police
search.
</P>
<P>
Noppadol Somboonsap, commissioner of the Narcotics Suppression
Bureau, told an Interior Ministry meeting Wednesday that his
anti-drug team had evidence that the officials in question were
involved in the amphetamine trade.
</P>
<P>
In several cases, amphetamines were found to have been
delivered to customers by cars bearing seals of certain agencies,
Noppadol said.
</P>
<P>
Noppadol has revealed those officials' names to Interior
Minister Sanoh Thiaenthong for further investigation, local
newspaper the Bangkok Post reported today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
