<HEADLINE> Thai Cement Group Joins Venture in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Siam Cement Group has
joined a consortium in China to establish a high-quality ceramic
wall-tile plant in Beijing, the group's Vice President Dusit
Nontanakorn announced here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Dusit said Beijing Cementhai Ceramic Co. (BCC) was established
to produce the tile under "Cotto" trademark. The total investment
is 1,043 million baht (29.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
BCC is a joint venture between the Siam Cement Public Company
Limited and Beijing General Corporation of Building Material
Group, the largest producer of construction materials in Beijing.
The Thai partner is holding 60 percent of the shares and the
Chinese partner 40 percent, Dusit said.
</P>
<P>
It is the fourth major project Siam has embarked on in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
