<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai-Indonesian Trade Up During January-June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Two-way trade between Thailand
and Indonesia during the first half of this year increased 14
percent from the same period of last year, according to a recent
report of the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia is Thailand's third largest market in ASEAN (the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations) after Singapore and
Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The half-year total trade value between the two countries stood
at 29 billion baht (1.14 billion US dollars), with Thailand
enjoying a surplus of 4.5 billion baht (176 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period of last year, Thailand's exports
to the country surged 12 percent while imports soared 17 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among Thailand's main export items were sugar, rice, chemicals
and engines, while import items included chemicals, coal and crude
oil.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
