<HEADLINE> British Film, Tourism Minister to Visit Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 9 (Xinhua) -- British Minister for Film and
Tourism Tom Clarke will visit Thailand on October 11-14 to
strengthen ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
This visit is one of a series of events to take place in the
next two months which will highlight Britain's commitment to
strengthening its political, commercial and cultural links with
Thailand, the British embassy in Bangkok announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Clarke will be in Phuket in southern Thailand on October 11-13,
where he will open Showcase Britain 1997, a travel trade fair
aimed at highlighting the attractions of Britain, local press
today quoted the embassy as saying.
</P>
<P>
The largest ever British travel trade mission to Asia will join
this event, with 65 British companies and 145 Asian delegates
participating.
</P>
<P>
The minister will arrive in Bangkok on October 14, where he
will meet senior officials and businessmen from the tourism
industry.
</P>
<P>
Clarke will then visit the British tourism authority's office
in Bangkok, and open a British food promotion activity in a
Bangkok hotel.  
</P>
