<HEADLINE> Maradona Refuses to Play in Anti-racism Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Soccer star Diego Maradona
has turned down an invitation to play in an exhibition tournament
in Madrid on Sunday as part of the European Union's anti-racism
year.
</P>
<P>
Maradona said he called the organizers to let them know his
decision: "I told them there were certain things I didn't like
about it so I'm not going to travel there," he said in a radio
interview.
</P>
<P>
Maradona was meant to captain one of three teams which will
play games divided into two 20-minute periods at Real Madrid's
Santiago Bernabeu stadium. The other captains are expected to be
Eric Cantona and George Weah.
</P>
<P>
The former Argentine captain, currently involved in another
doping scandal, did not give any further reasons for his absence.
</P>
<P>
Maradona, who turns 37 this month, has missed the last three
games for local club Boca Juniors with a leg injury.
</P>
<P>
He faces a possible ban - the third of his career - for testing
positive for "illegal substances" after the first game of the
season in August against Argentinos Juniors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
