<HEADLINE> Two Bombs Explode in Colombian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Two bombs exploded
today in the Colombian capital, a day after the country was placed
on an alert due to growing violence surrounding the impending
local elections.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported in the blasts.
</P>
<P>
Colombian police said urban commandos from one of Colombia's
two leading guerrilla groups were believed responsible for the
explosions which blew up outside downtown offices of two political
candidates.
</P>
<P>
The terrorist attacks are intended to disrupt the October 26
elections for mayors, town councillors and governors.
</P>
<P>
Colombian President Ernesto Samper announced a "red alert" in
the country on Tuesday night after 28 policemen and soliders were
killed in two attacks last weekend. 
</P>
