<HEADLINE> Thailand to Borrow More Loans to Fund Cash-Strapped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Thailand plans to borrow more
loans from offshore to fund cash-strapped businesses whose main
earnings are from exports, according to the Thai Finance Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Finance Ministry may either borrow directly from
overseas sources or guarantee offshore loans to be borrowed by the
Industrial Finance Corporation of Thailand or Export and Import
Bank, Deputy Finance Minister Chaturon Chaisaeng was quoted today
by local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
The plan will force the ministry to rise its foreign borrowing
ceiling for 1997, which was set at 4.1 billion US dollars -- all
of which will be used to finance basic infrastructure
construction.  
</P>
