<HEADLINE> Beijing Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers are as follows:
</P>
<P>
 People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin said yesterday that great progress has
been made in Sino-US relations over the past year, especially in
bilateral economic and trade co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Both China and the US should continue their efforts to ensure a
long-term and stable development of bilateral economic and trade
relations, he said during a meeting with visiting US Commerce
Secretary William Daley.
</P>
<P>
-- As autumn harvest is approaching, the State Council issued a
circular yesterday, urging localities to earnestly carry out
government grain purchase policies so as to protect farmers'
interests.
</P>
<P>
The circular demands the purchase prices for autumn grain
remain at the same level of last year, and surplus grains outside
the state-set quotas should be purchased at the government
protective prices. Any violations should be severely punished.
</P>
<P>
 Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Li Peng expressed his satisfaction with the
smooth development of Sino-Indonesian ties yesterday during his
meeting with Indonesian Minister of Defense and Security Edi
Sudrajat.
</P>
<P>
Li also expressed the Chinese government's concern for losses
resulting from the forest fire in Indonesia. He said that under
the leadership of President Soeharto and the Indonesian
government, the Indonesian people will surely conquer the disaster.
</P>
<P>
