<P>
ALMA-ATA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan is willing to
strengthen its ties with China and participate in an all-round
cooperation, Senate Speaker of the Republic of Kazakhstan Omirbek
Baigeldiyev said here today.
</P>
<P>
Baigeldiyev made the remark while meeting with Yang Zhenya,
Vice Chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress, who arrived here this morning from the
Republic of Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng's earlier visit to Kazakhstan marked
the beginning of a new stage of Sino-Kazakhstan cooperation,
Baigeldiyev said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed appreciation for the traditional friendship
between the two countries and the rapid development of their ties
since Kazakhstan's independence five years ago.
</P>
<P>
The large-scale cooperation programs to be carried out between
the two countries have drawn worldwide attention, said the
Speaker, referring particularly to the agreements reached by the
two nations in the field of petroleum.
</P>
<P>
The two neighboring countries complement each other
economically in addition to sharing geographical advantages that
can favorably influence economic and trade cooperation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Both the Chinese government and the National People's Congress
attach great importance to developing friendly and cooperative
relationships with Kazakhstan, Yang pointed out. 
