<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Central Sulawesi, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A tectonic earthquake measuring
5.0 on the Richter scale Wednesday night jolted Palu, capital of
Indonesia's central Sulawesi province.
</P>
<P>
The quake occurred at 22:29 local time. Some of the city
residents were surprised when they felt the tremors and ran out of
their houses, the Meteorological and Geophysical Agency in Jakarta
said today.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake was located at the Makassar Straits about 119.72
degrees of the east longitude and 0.21 degrees of the south
latitude at a normal depth, some 50 kilometers north of Dongala,
the agency said.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate information on losses or casualties.
</P>
</TEXT>
