<HEADLINE> Nigerian Warplane Bombs Sierra Leonean Military Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A Nigerian warplane today
bombarded a Sierra Leonean army base west of Freetown, killing at
least four people.
</P>
<P>
Two soldiers and two civilians were killed and 28 others
injured in the attack, said reports reaching here from Freetown,
capital of Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The plane fired seven rockets and heavily damaged the base
where Sierra Leonean junta leader Major Johnny Koroma and other
high-ranking military officers were about to have a meeting.
</P>
<P>
A military spokesman for the junta said that the attack was an
assassination attempt on Koroma, who seized power in a coup in May
this year.
</P>
<P>
A Nigeria-led West African force has been imposing a military
and economic embargo on Sierra Leone in a bid to force the junta
to step down. 
