<HEADLINE> Police Seize 1.5 Tons of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Guatemala police impounded
1.5 tons of cocaine today in its northern department of Izabel,
according to reports reaching here from Guatemala City.
</P>
<P>
This was believed to be the largest amount of drugs confiscated
this year. Besides the cocaine, which has a street value of 23
million dollars, police also seized large amounts of firearms and
ammunition.
</P>
<P>
Police exchanged heavy gunfire with the drug traffickers for
several hours. One gunman was killed while six others fled.
</P>
<P>
Police and the armed forces have decided to launch a joint
operation to hunt for the traffickers at large.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala has so far seized 4.23 tons of cocaine, 2.37 tons of
marijuana and 9 kilograms of heroin and captured 247 drug dealers,
the reports said. 
