<HEADLINE> Chile to Boost Spending in Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Chile will increase spending on
tourism in 1998 to help promote its tourist industry.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Economy Alvaro Garcia said today the country needs
to develop tourism through the joint efforts of the public and
private tourist sectors.
</P>
<P>
Garcia said the National Tourist Service is focusing on
improving the country's tourism, which is the fifth largest
foreign currency earner in the country at nearly 2.5 billion
U.S. dollars a year.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the period of January to August, the flow
of domestic and foreign visitors into the country increased 14.2
percent, compared with the same period last year, while tourism
revenues jumped 80 percent from 1.1 billion dollars in 1996 to
2.07 billion in January-August 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Director of the National Tourism Service Cesar Gomez said
the number of foreign tourists visiting the country reached 1.2
million in the first eight months of this year. 
