years, was seeking a 10 million-dollar deal.
</P>
<P>
The Bulls wanted a contract loaded with incentives that would
boost Rodman's payoff if he stayed out of trouble, avoided the
suspensions and injuries that plagued him much of last season.
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old Rodman had suggested the Bulls not pay him
until the end of the season, holding 10 million dollars in reserve
and deducting money from the sum for fines and suspensions. NBA
rules forbid such a move.
</P>
<P>
One of the reasons that the Bulls are interested in Rodman is
Scottie Pippen got injuried. Pippen underwent foot surgery on
Monday and might not be back in uniform until mid-January. The new
season opens October 31. 
