<HEADLINE> French Grand Prix Excluded from 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The International Automobile
Federation (FIA) ommited the French Grand Prix from the 1998's
Formula One world championship calendar on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jacques Regis, president of the French Automobile Federation
(FFSA), said that the FIA had decided to exclude France in the
calendar according to a dispute over television rights.
</P>
<P>
French channel TF1 has the rights for Formula One in France but
French state channel FR3 obtained a judgement allowing all the TV
channels to operate on the site.
</P>
<P>
Last year the French Grand Prix was given a tentative spot on
the calendar and the problems were resolved to hold th erace.
</P>
<P>
The FIA had warned that unless the conflict was resolved France
would not appear on the 1998 calendar.
</P>
<P>
It is not the first time the French Grand Prix was taken off
the schedule. In 1992 FIA was threatened with law suits by the
anti-tabacco law because of cigarette sponsorship showing on
cars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
