<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Successful in Seedless-Grape Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A new variety of seedless grape
has been developed in east China's Anhui province.
</P>
<P>
Three years of experiments have shown that the seedless grapes
weigh more than 20 g. on average and some even as much as 30 g.,
compared to 2 to 4 g. for ordinary seedless grapes each.
</P>
<P>
The new grape is the brainchild of Zhong Jiahuang, a professor
at Anhui Agriculture University, who found a new way to get
varieties of grapes with seeds to bear seedless fruit.
</P>
<P>
The Jingya variety produces 95 percent seedless grapes and has
a maturation time that is 10 days earlier than usual, greatly
improving economic returns.
</P>
<P>
The grape is also suited to the weather conditions of south
China, unlike other seedless types.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971009.0309 </DOCNO>
