<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investors Eye North China Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 9 (Xinhua)-- The Economic and
Technological Development Zone in Qinhuangdao, a port city in
north China's Hebei province, has benefited from Hong Kong
investment, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Out of 30 Hong Kong enterprises involved in industrial
development in the zone, eight have an annual output value of more
than 10 million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
One joint venture sells more than 70 per cent of its decorative
glass in Europe, the United States, and Southeast Asia, with
annual sales of over 10 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
A Hong Kong synthetic leather producer has a nationwide sales
networks centered on Qinhuangdao with output of more than 100
million yuan and pre-tax profit of 10 million yuan over the past
four years.
</P>
<P>
For further expansion, the Hong Kong company invested 13
million US dollars on a second-phase project, bringing another 300
million yuan in added value, and 45 million yuan in pre-tax profit.
</P>
<P>
Some Hong Kong investors have used the zone's preferential
policies to invest in real estate, commerce, and transport.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is the largest overseas investor in the zone. Out of
300 overseas-funded projects in the zone, 105 are backed by Hong
Kong companies, with 500 million US dollars in capital.
</P>
<P>
Sectors attracting investors are metallurgy, machine building,
electronics, chemicals, textiles, and construction. Also popular
are glass, ship repairs, and hi-tech products, because local
conditions are especially suitable for them.  
</P>
</TEXT>
