Mantilla was the second seed to be upset after the earlier exit
of 5th-seed Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten, who was eliminated by the
Czech Republic's Bohdan Ulihrach 4-6, 4-6.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Henman, who ranked 21 in the world but unseeded
here, was a quarter-finalist at this year's Australian Open. He
aimed at his third tournament win this year after victories in
Sydney and Tashkent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
