<HEADLINE> IDB Finances Microenterprises in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of 5 million
U.S. dollars in nonreimbursable financing to Brazil to help
provide credit to low-income microentrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
The program will lay the groundwork for a much larger project
by Banco Nacional de Desnvolvimento Economico c Social, which is
committed to providing 60 million dollars in credit to the
microenterprise sector.
</P>
<P>
The IDB financing, to be disbursed in local currency, will
support the development and strengthening of first tier lending
institutions, including nongovernment organizations, and
intermediate financial institutions that provide credit to
microenterprise, an important source of employment and economic
growth in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
